'''Azzopardi''' is a [[Jewish]] [[surname]] derived from ''A Safardi'', which means "A Jew coming from [[Spain]]". The surname is found in the [[Maltese Islands]]. Most of the Azzopardi families in Malta originated in Toledano, [[Spain]].

Though Jewish in origin, most of the families converted to [[Catholicism]] in [[1492]] when the Jews were expelled from Malta, while those that refused had to leave the Islands. A few of the families that remained are known to have practised Judaism in secret, but these families eventually converted fully to Catholicism.


